  "commentary": "With SPX at 6556 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6550 (-10,040M) and max positive gamma at 6580 (+1,403M), dealers are in active hedging mode—buying the dip toward 6550 and will aggressively sell any push toward 6580. The breakout regime with massive negative GEX (-65.3B) means dealer hedging will amplify any directional moves, creating volatile, trending behavior rather than mean reversion. Key levels to watch are the 6550 max negative gamma floor where buying pressure intensifies, and the 6580 resistance where dealer selling kicks in hard.\n\nBottom line: expect violent swings between 6550 and 6580 with momentum likely to continue in whatever direction breaks first.",
